# 📘 Cybersecurity Study Guide Matrix by Role & Level

| **Level**       | **Hat Role** | **Certification**         | **Recommended Study Guides / Platforms**                                                                 |
|-----------------|--------------|----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 🟢 Entry-Level  | Blue Hat     | Security+, CCST, SC-900    | - CompTIA CertMaster Learn<br>- Professor Messer videos<br>- Microsoft Learn modules                     |
|                 | Red Hat      | TryHackMe Pre-Security     | - TryHackMe Pre-Security labs<br>- TCM Practical Help Desk course                                    |
|                 | Purple Hat   | EC-Council Essentials, FCF | - CodeRed Essentials Series<br>- Fortinet NSE Institute<br>- Google Cybersecurity Certificate            |

| 🟡 Intermediate | Blue Hat     | CySA+, CyberOps Associate  | - CompTIA CySA+ Study Guide (Sybex)<br>- Cisco NetAcad<br>- TCM SOC Analyst Roadmap                  |
|                 | Red Hat      | Pentest+, CEH, CPTS        | - Georgia Weidman’s *Penetration Testing* book<br>- Hacker Playbook 3<br>- TryHackMe Offensive Path      |
|                 | Purple Hat   | SC-900, PortSwigger Labs   | - Microsoft Learn SC-900<br>- OWASP Top 10 + PortSwigger Academy<br>- GitHub Advanced Security Pathway   |

| 🔴 Advanced     | Blue Hat     | CCNP Security, GCIH        | - Cisco Press CCNP guides<br>- SANS Blue Team Field Manual<br>- GIAC GCIH courseware                    |
|                 | Red Hat      | OSCP, LPT, GPEN            | - Offensive Security PWK (OSCP)<br>- EC-Council LPT Elite modules<br>- SANS GPEN courseware              |
|                 | Purple Hat   | CISSP, CISM, Responsible AI| - CISSP All-in-One (Shon Harris)<br>- ISACA CISM Review Manual<br>- Microsoft Responsible AI modules|

A Business Peer recommended I shouldn't focus exclusively on CISCO. He advised I pursue training on Udemy.Here is a response from Grok.
Copilot & Grok

# 🛡️ Cybersecurity Learning Path & Roadmap (Udemy-Based)

A structured, self-paced roadmap for aspiring cybersecurity professionals. Ideal for beginners progressing toward Junior Cybersecurity Analyst roles. Courses are curated from Udemy, with hands-on labs, certifications, and career milestones.

---

## 📦 Overview

- **Duration**: 6–12 months (10–15 hrs/week)
- **Tools Needed**:
  - Internet-connected computer
  - VirtualBox or similar VM software
  - GitHub account for tracking
- **Progress Tracking**: Use Markdown checklists in your GitHub repo.

---

## 🧠 Prerequisites (1–2 Weeks)

| Resource | Description | Link |
|---------|-------------|------|
| Roadmap to Begin in Cybersecurity | Free intro to cybersecurity concepts | [Udemy](https://www.udemy.com/course/roadmap-to-begin-in-cybersecurity/) |

**Skills to Gain**:
- Basic OS navigation
- Networking fundamentals
- Threat awareness (phishing, malware)

---

## 🚀 Part 1: Beginner Level (0–3 Months)

**Milestones**:
- Complete CompTIA Security+ prep
- Set up a basic home lab

### 📚 Recommended Courses

| Title | Instructor | Duration | Link |
|-------|------------|----------|------|
| Cyber Security: From Beginner to Expert | Logix Academy | Varies | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/cybersecurity-from-beginner-to-expert/) |
| Absolute Beginners Guide to Cyber Security | Alexander Oni | 4–6 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/the-absolute-beginners-guide-to-information-cyber-security/) |
| Hackers Exposed! (Vol. 1) | Nathan House | 12 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/the-complete-cyber-security-course/) |
| CompTIA Security+ (SY0-701) | Jason Dion | 20+ hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/securityplus/) |
| 2-Hour Crash Course | — | 2 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/cyberintro/) |

**Skills to Develop**:
- Threat identification
- Encryption & firewalls
- Risk assessment

**Project**: Create a security audit report for your home network.

---

## 🔐 Part 2: Intermediate Level (3–6 Months)

**Milestones**:
- Earn CySA+ or PenTest+ cert
- Build ethical hacking portfolio

### 📚 Recommended Courses

| Title | Instructor | Duration | Link |
|-------|------------|----------|------|
| Network Security (Vol. 2) | Nathan House | 12 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/network-security-course/) |
| Ethical Hacking From Scratch | Zaid Sabih | 15 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/learn-ethical-hacking-from-scratch/) |
| End Point Protection (Vol. 3) | Nathan House | 10 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/end-point-protection/) |
| PenTest+ (PT0-002) | — | 15 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/comptia-pentest-exams-002/) |
| Certified in Cybersecurity (ISC2) | Thor Pedersen | 10 hrs | [Course](https://www.udemy.com/course/certifiedincybersecurity/) |

**Skills to Develop**:
- SIEM tools
- Vulnerability scanning
- Incident response

**Project**: Simulate a penetration test and document findings in GitHub.

---

## 🧠 Part 3: Advanced Level (6+ Months)

**Milestones**:
